    <!-- Story 3.4: Voice command help system - comprehensive grouped announcements -->
    <string name="help_command_introduction">Available voice commands. Commands are organized into four groups.</string>
    <string name="help_command_recognition_group">For recognizing objects, say: Recognize, to identify objects in your camera view. What do I see, to hear the last recognition result again. Repeat, to hear the last announcement again.</string>
    <string name="help_command_navigation_group">For navigation, say: Navigate, to start turn-by-turn directions. Where am I, to hear your current location. Cancel, to stop navigation or recognition.</string>
    <string name="help_command_settings_group">For adjusting settings, say: Settings, to open preferences. High contrast on or High contrast off, to toggle visual mode. Increase speed or Decrease speed, to adjust speech rate. Large text on or Large text off, to change text size. Haptic off, light, medium, or strong, to adjust vibration intensity.</string>
    <string name="help_command_general_group">For general actions, say: History, to review past recognitions. Save location, to bookmark your current place. Back, to go back. Home, to return to the home screen.</string>
    <string name="help_command_conclusion">Say a command now, or tap the microphone button to exit voice mode.</string>
